Generalised anxiety disorder or GAD, is essentially defined by excessive worrying.

1
00:00:12,170 --> 00:00:14,820
And this is tricky because we all worry, right?

2
00:00:14,820 --> 00:00:18,009
From time to time, we all worry about stuff.

3
00:00:18,009 --> 00:00:23,290
This disorder sort of epitomises the difficulty with the anxiety disorders in terms of drawing

4
00:00:23,290 --> 00:00:28,640
that line between what is within the broad parameters of normal anxiety and what is clinically

5
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,880
significant anxiety.

6
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:35,760
Some of the differences with generalised anxiety disorder and non-clinical worrying would be

7
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:40,700
that people who have generalised anxiety disorder may tell you that they experience their worry

8
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:43,150
as totally uncontrollable.

9
00:00:43,150 --> 00:00:47,010
They&#39;ll say things like, “I can’t get to sleep at night because I can&#39;t turn my

10
00:00:47,010 --> 00:00:48,120
mind off&quot;.

11
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:53,150
Now, if you&#39;re sitting there thinking, &quot;Oh boy, I’ve felt like that in the past – maybe

12
